The paper deals with interference networks and communication channels, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of feedback links and vector quantization techniques also suggests the Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the achievable spatial multiplexing gain, which is a performance metric often studied in the Computer Engineering (cs.CE) sub-category.
